pageTitle: Bibleman: Lambasting the Legions of Laziness Review by The Dove Foundation
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {41835=Video Release: 8/1/2008, 47006=Copyright © 2010 - The Dove Foundation - all rights reserved Review syndication authorized for ChristianCinema.com, 42621=Synopsis: What kind of villain has trouble staying awake long enough to disrupt the lives of impressionable kids? How could a snoozy senior citizen possibly pose a problem for vibrant, healthy youngsters? Meet The Slacker. Drew has been skipping the Youth Bible Study lately, causing concern to the Bible Adventure Team (otherwise known as Bibleman, Biblegirl, Cypher and Melody). And just how will Bibleman counteract the Laser of Laziness, which has paralyzed his colleagues? Don't miss a minute of this sleepy-er, gripping adventure as a young man's heart and soul hang in the balance. And be very careful when visiting HelpingHotline.com. Key verse: Proverbs 18:9 "The person who is 'slack' in his work is just like a person who destroys."}
